reviews.text: Nice food. A hidden gem in this area. As a Hong Kong local style restaurant you shouldn't expect any nice service here. Octopus card is accepted apart from cash. Price for dinner set is reasonable and come with soup and drink. Most dishes are priced from seventy or eighty dollars, but no drink is included for that price. Generally crowded between seven and nine in the evening.
Expensive but some dishes are good and large in size.
Supersize meal! It is good value for money!!!
Ordinary HK style tea restaurant within the district
Good
